Rating: 4
I needed a recipe for breakfast Christmas morning and I had a panettone... This is just excellent. Watch pan- frying the bread because it browns fast; just soaked the raisins in hot water rather than brandy and they plumped up beautifully. Makes 6 large servings; I made it Christmas Eve and re-heated it Christmas morning - rather than waiting for the whole thing to heat through in the oven, just cut in large squares and heat in microwave for 1 & 1/2 minutes each. Delicious, not soggy, everyone loved it. Ina has a similar recipe on foodnetwork dot com using almonds, but this is a keeper!You won't be disappointed and a great way to use up 1/2 of a 2-lb. panettone!

Rating: 4
Fantastic. I'm a big fan of bread pudding to begin with but I made this for breakfast on Christmas morning and it was perfect. I had to cook it about 10 minutes longer to dry the bread out as after the suggested time it was still too wet in the middle. But great flavor and not too sweet. Delicious.